video.title: DC's Legends of Tomorrow
video.synopsis: A mysterious "time master" from the future unites an unlikely group of superheroes and villains to save the world from a powerful evil.

episodes.synopsis: Arriving back from the future, rascal Rip Hunter gathers a legendary motley crew to stop an eternal villain from wiping out all of time and history.
episodes.title: Pilot: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: On a risky mission to undermine Savage, Atom's suit falls into the wrong hands, and Stein must confer with a brilliant man: his younger self.
episodes.title: Pilot: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Trouble finds Rip and Sara when they try to seize Savage's financial resources. Snart and Rory try to steal a priceless emerald. Stein mentors Ray.
episodes.title: Blood Ties

episodes.synopsis: The team arrives in 1986 and follows Savage's trail to a Soviet scientist. Rip squares off with a mentor. Kendra struggles to control her new urges.
episodes.title: White Knights

episodes.synopsis: The team gets outside help to infiltrate the gulag. Sara agrees to execute a harsh backup plan if needed. Valentina learns Stein is half of Firestorm.
episodes.title: Fail-Safe

episodes.synopsis: When the Waverider lands in 2046, Rip and the crew get a bleak vision of Star City's future, and Sara searches for the vanished Oliver Queen.
episodes.title: Star City 2046

episodes.synopsis: When the team receives a distress call from another time master stranded in deep space, Rip decides to respond -- even though it may be a trap.
episodes.title: Marooned

episodes.synopsis: In 1950s Oregon, Professor Stein and Sara go undercover at a hospital where Savage is working, suspecting that he's behind a recent string of murders.
episodes.title: Night of the Hawk

episodes.synopsis: The Waverider leaves Sara, Ray and Kendra behind in the 1950s. When no one comes back for them, Sara decides to return to the League of Assassins.
episodes.title: Left Behind

episodes.synopsis: The team must take out one of Savage's future allies, but they're confronted with a moral dilemma when they learn more about him.
episodes.title: Progeny

episodes.synopsis: When Rip and the team head to the Old West to lay low, they end up tangling with a gang of outlaws and putting the town in danger.
episodes.title: The Magnificent Eight

episodes.synopsis: The Time Masters send the Pilgrim on a mission to assassinate each of the team members, targeting their younger, more vulnerable selves.
episodes.title: Last Refuge

episodes.synopsis: Rip and the team travel to 2166 London, where Savage is at the height of his power, in what may be their final opportunity to take him down.
episodes.title: Leviathan

episodes.synopsis: Savage tells Kendra he can reunite her with Carter, and Rip and the team weigh their options for dealing with him.
episodes.title: River of Time

episodes.synopsis: Being in the vicinity of the Time Masters leaves both Rip and Rory incredibly disturbed. Meanwhile, Sara takes over the Waverider.
episodes.title: Destiny

episodes.synopsis: Rip and the team return to 2016, where they each weigh whether to continue their mission. Sara has an emotional reunion with her father.
episodes.title: Legendary

episodes.synopsis: In 1942, the Legends scramble to protect Albert Einstein and thwart a plot by Nazis and Damien Darhk to obliterate New York City with an atomic bomb.
episodes.title: Out of Time

episodes.synopsis: Still in 1942, the team does battle with a Nazi berserker to save the Justice Society of America -- including Nate's grandfather -- from disaster.
episodes.title: The Justice Society of America

episodes.synopsis: After a mishap sends them to feudal Japan, the team must help Nate control his new superpowers to protect a village against a fierce warlord.
episodes.title: Shogun

episodes.synopsis: With the course of the Civil War in jeopardy, Jax and Amaya travel to a slaveholding plantation while the other Legends battle Confederate zombies.
episodes.title: Abominations

episodes.synopsis: Infiltrating the White House in 1987, the team finds Damien Darhk subverting a treaty with the USSR, and Stein's younger self lands in mortal danger.
episodes.title: Compromised

episodes.synopsis: In the Wild West, the Legends team up with an old ally to fight a gunslinger with plans to use the power of a mysterious ore to rule his own country.
episodes.title: Outlaw Country

episodes.synopsis: Teamed up with Flash and other meta-humans, the Legends travel to 1951 to abduct a Dominator, but unwittingly precipitate a final showdown.
episodes.title: Invasion!

episodes.synopsis: When Damien Darhk and a new ally make a pact with Al Capone, the Legends set course for 1920s Chicago, where a sinister plot begins to unfold.
episodes.title: The Chicago Way

episodes.synopsis: After Darhk attacks in 1967, film student George Lucas gives up moviemaking, an Aberration that threatens the existence of the Legends themselves.
episodes.title: Raiders of the Lost Art

episodes.synopsis: Strife splinters the Legion of Doom as they track down the Spear of Destiny. Stein breaks the rules of time travel to get his daughter's help.
episodes.title: The Legion of Doom

episodes.synopsis: The Legends set course for 1776 to thwart the assassination of George Washington and face a traitorous old friend who's after the Spear of Destiny.
episodes.title: Turncoat

episodes.synopsis: Skipping from the 31st century to the 6th in a quest for Spear of Destiny fragments, the Legends team up with an old ally in King Arthur's court.
episodes.title: Camelot/3000

episodes.synopsis: Crashing millions of years in the past, the Legends tangle with dinosaurs while fighting evil versions of themselves inside Rip Hunter's twisted mind.
episodes.title: Land of the Lost

episodes.synopsis: Searching for Commander Steel's Spear of Destiny fragment, the team infiltrates NASA in 1970 and intervenes in the Apollo 13 mission to the moon.
episodes.title: Moonshot

episodes.synopsis: To destroy the Spear of Destiny, the team seeks out J.R.R. Tolkien at the front during World War I. But the power of the Spear seduces one their own.
episodes.title: Fellowship of the Spear

episodes.synopsis: As the Legion of Doom lords over Star City, the Legends discover that reality has been rewritten and rally to steal back the Spear of Destiny.
episodes.title: Doomworld

episodes.synopsis: Racing an altered-reality wave from 2017, the Legends return to France during World War I to steal the Spear from earlier versions of themselves.
episodes.title: Aruba

episodes.synopsis: Rip Hunter forms the Time Bureau to repair the timeline broken by the Legends, who now race to prevent Julius Caesar from conquering the 21st century.
episodes.title: Aruba-Con

episodes.synopsis: The Legends travel to P.T. Barnum's circus in 1870 to hunt down a dangerous time anachronism. Amaya makes a distressing confession to the team.
episodes.title: Freakshow

episodes.synopsis: In 2042, a time when metahumans are outlawed, the team tracks a mysterious assassin. Amaya takes a trippy vision quest to understand her totem.
episodes.title: Zari

episodes.synopsis: Joined by a spirited new team member, the Legends jump to 1988 to capture an anachronistic Dominator and save young Ray from being killed.
episodes.title: Phone Home

episodes.synopsis: Rip Hunter recruits the Legends to help him track a vampire in 19th-century London, but they soon encounter an old -- and much more dangerous -- foe.
episodes.title: Return of the Mack

episodes.synopsis: The Legends set course to save Hollywood's Golden Age -- and the future of technology -- after mythical beauty Helen of Troy sparks a Tinseltown war.
episodes.title: Helen Hunt

episodes.synopsis: Mick confronts painful family memories when the Legends travel to 1967 to stop an extraordinary foe from turning the Vietnam War into World War III.
episodes.title: Welcome to the Jungle

episodes.synopsis: Rallying alongside Supergirl, the Flash and their surprising new ally, the Legends face a climactic showdown with the threat from Earth-X.
episodes.title: Crisis on Earth-X, Part 4

episodes.synopsis: Reeling from a dreadful loss, the Legends travel to a Viking outpost in North America where a strange artifact could change the fate of the New World.
episodes.title: Beebo the God of War

episodes.synopsis: Stuck in an asylum in 1969, Sara and Constantine battle the demon Mallus while Zari and Ray fight the fiend in 2017. Meanwhile, Amaya confronts Kuasa.
episodes.title: Daddy Darhkest

episodes.synopsis: With the Waverider stuck in a time loop, Zari must decipher clues hidden among the crew's personal secrets to save the ship from disaster.
episodes.title: Here I Go Again

episodes.synopsis: In search of Zambesi's powerful earth totem, the Legends swashbuckle their way through 1717 with Blackbeard and his band of lusty buccaneers.
episodes.title: The Curse of the Earth Totem

episodes.synopsis: Using Ray to smuggle a scientist out of East Berlin, Nora and Damien Darhk square off against an assassin -- a younger version of Darhk himself.
episodes.title: No Country for Old Dads

episodes.synopsis: When a lost totem usurps Elvis Presley's music, the Legends set the dial to 1950s Memphis to save the King's career and the future of rock 'n' roll.
episodes.title: Amazing Grace

episodes.synopsis: Constantine returns to help the Legends when Mallus leverages the power of the death totem -- through Sara -- to mount an attack aboard the Waverider.
episodes.title: Necromancing the Stone

episodes.synopsis: Nate and Wally form a risky alliance to recover Amaya's stolen totem. Sara, Ray and Gary uncover an alarming secret about Ava.
episodes.title: I, Ava

episodes.synopsis: While Amaya goes rogue to save her village, the team races to protect a young Barack Obama and thwart Mallus -- with a little help from a noted actor.
episodes.title: Guest Starring John Noble

episodes.synopsis: Pirates, Vikings, Romans and the Legends all collide in the Wild West as the team scrambles to use the totems to vanquish Mallus once and for all.
episodes.title: The Good, The Bad and The Cuddly

episodes.synopsis: Encountering a psychedelic magical beast at Woodstock in 1969, the Legends call on John Constantine -- and chaste Gary -- to prevent a massacre.
episodes.title: The Virgin Gary

episodes.synopsis: Finding themselves in Salem, Massachusetts, during the infamous witch trials, the Legends come across a magical being with a gift for song.
episodes.title: Witch Hunt

episodes.synopsis: Chasing a magical creature in 1970s London, buttoned-down Ray tries to infiltrate a notorious punk band. Nate discovers the Time Bureau's wild side.
episodes.title: Dancing Queen

episodes.synopsis: The team lands in a hair-raising campfire story when a monster in the woods starts snatching kids from a summer camp in 1990s Maine.
episodes.title: Wet Hot American Bummer

episodes.synopsis: A monster-film director joins the Legends' fight when a nightmare comes to life in Tokyo Bay in 1951. Ray calls in a risky favor to revive Constantine.
episodes.title: Tagumo Attacks!!!

episodes.synopsis: After a surprise inspection on the Waverider, Hank joins the team in 1920s Paris to hunt down a monster -- with a little help from Ernest Hemingway.
episodes.title: Tender Is the Nate

episodes.synopsis: There's a murderer on the loose in 1850s New Orleans, and the cops suspect a powerful voodoo priestess. But the real killer is something else entirely.
episodes.title: Hell No, Dolly

episodes.synopsis: Discovering that his meddling has changed the Legends into trigger-happy killers, Constantine turns to Charlie for help re-altering the timeline.
episodes.title: Legends	of To-Meow-Meow

episodes.synopsis: While treachery rocks the Time Bureau, Mona joins the Legends as they track a ferocious escaped creature to the lucha libre rings of 1960s Mexico City.
episodes.title: Lucha de Apuestas

episodes.synopsis: With Hank hot on their trail, the Legends jump to 1973 to kidnap President Nixon after he develops a timeline-threatening honest streak.
episodes.title: The	Getaway

episodes.synopsis: An outbreak of lust leads the ladies to 1800s England, where Jane Austen has stopped writing about romance. Rory and Constantine summon a spirit.
episodes.title: Sance & Sensibility

episodes.synopsis: Sara journeys to an otherworldly limbo to save Ava, Nate makes a surprising discovery about Hank, and Nora helps the Legends take on a demon.
episodes.title: The	Eggplant, the	Witch & the Wardrobe

episodes.synopsis: While Ray fights off demon possession and Mick attends a romance novelist convention, Nate and Zari go on a mission to a 1930s adventurer's club.
episodes.title: Egg	MacGuffin

episodes.synopsis: After setting a trap for the Waverider, Neron forces Constantine into a showdown with an ancient Celtic king. Gary nip-notizes the Time Bureau.
episodes.title: Nip/Stuck

episodes.synopsis: While Constantine fast-talks his way through hell, Neron unleashes a tech-savvy plan to harvest souls and the Fairy Godmother helps Gary get revenge.
episodes.title: Terms of Service

episodes.synopsis: The Legends make a family-friendly plan to thwart Neron's scheme to unleash hell on Earth. Constantine and Nora race to save Ray's soul.
episodes.title: Hey,	World!

episodes.synopsis: Thrown together in a strange new world and united by grief, the Legends and their Paragon allies rally for a final showdown with the Anti-Monitor.
episodes.title: Crisis on Infinite Earths: Hour Five

episodes.synopsis: With a documentary film crew in tow and Gideon on the fritz, the Legends travel to imperial Russia when the funeral of Rasputin takes a fiendish turn.
episodes.title: Meet The Legends

episodes.synopsis: Discovering Astra's hellish plan, the team hits 1940s Los Angeles to ice a notorious gangster back from the dead. Behrad's family gives Nate a shock.
episodes.title: Miss Me, Kiss Me, Love Me

episodes.synopsis: A double-time-jump mission takes the crew to 1989 and 2004 to keep the infamous Prom Night Slasher from turning a high school bash into a bloodbath.
episodes.title: Slay Anything

episodes.synopsis: Constantine's past haunts him  literally  while the other Legends track a cunning Encore to an opulent soiree during the French Revolution.
episodes.title: A Head of Her Time

episodes.synopsis: Still lusting for conquest, a resurrected Genghis Khan moves on Triad territory in 1990s Hong Kong. Constantine seeks a cure for his sudden affliction.
episodes.title: Mortal Khanbat

episodes.synopsis: Nora mires the team in an elaborate web of lies when her father, Damien Darhk, returns as an Encore. Zari helps Mick with a troll problem.
episodes.title: Mr. Parker's Cul-De-Sac

episodes.synopsis: While Ray struggles to break big news to Nate, the Waverider travels to Elizabethan London to find William Shakespeare and a piece of the Loom of Fate.
episodes.title: Romeo v. Juliet: Dawn of Justness

episodes.synopsis: Zari learns about her alt-past while Mick tries to alter his own. Charlie's murderous sister hunts the team to recover a piece of the Loom of Fate.
episodes.title: Zari, Not Zari

episodes.synopsis: Chasing Lachesis's ring through time, Constantine and Zari run into trouble in a Victorian boarding house. Gary, Ava and Mick risk a trip to hell.
episodes.title: The Great British Fake Off

episodes.synopsis: Mick and Lita try to have a father-daughter weekend while Sara struggles with a frightening new skill and a sinister force stalks a disabled Waverider.
episodes.title: Ship Broken

episodes.synopsis: The Legends hit a college campus to get their hands on the Chalice of Dionysus  but first they must win an epic fraternity drinking contest.
episodes.title: Freaks & Greeks

episodes.synopsis: Now immortal for a day, the Legends race to use the Loom of Time, but a betrayal  and hordes of undead  stand in the way. Gary faces the Fates alone.
episodes.title: I Am Legends

episodes.synopsis: In a dystopian world tyrannized by the Fates, the Legends find themselves imprisoned inside popular TV shows, struggling to remember their true selves.
episodes.title: The One Where We're Trapped on TV

episodes.synopsis: In a time-traveling showdown, the Legends race to save Charlie, overthrow the Fates and restore humanity's free will once and for all.
episodes.title: Swan Thong

episodes.synopsis: After aliens whisk Sara away from 1977 London, Ava and the Legends chase down leads to her whereabouts  and uncover a very peculiar thing about Gary.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: Sara and Gary explore a bizarre alien planet, while new Legend Spooner helps the team uncover a sinister secret in a 1950s California burger joint.
episodes.title: Meat: the Legends

episodes.synopsis: Zari and John take center stage on a popular televised singing competition to force a musical showdown with an alien invader bent on conquering Earth.
episodes.title: The Ex-Factor

episodes.synopsis: Chasing down an alien during the Cuban Missile Crisis, the team tries to de-escalate Cold War tensions, but their every step only makes things worse.
episodes.title: Bay of Squids

episodes.synopsis: Sara gets a preview of Bishop's twisted plans for humanity's future. Agitated by mortal life, Astra makes a dubious magical deal with Aleister Crowley.
episodes.title: The Satanist's Apprentice

episodes.synopsis: With Mick tracking Sara, the others disguise John's mansion as a 1950s mental health facility to interrogate an alien masquerading as Amelia Earhart.
episodes.title: Bishop's Gambit

episodes.synopsis: Bishop hands Sara a nasty surprise, and Behrad leads the team back to 1970s London on a half-baked preemptive rescue mission.
episodes.title: Back to the Finale Part II

episodes.synopsis: Tracking an alien to 1891, the Legends find history turned on its head in the not-so-Wild West. John leans on Gary to help him find a mythic fountain.
episodes.title: Stressed Western

episodes.synopsis: Mick gets a big surprise when the crew time-jumps to 2023. Behrad tries to save his favorite sitcom from the influence of a cute, pink, fuzzy alien.
episodes.title: This is Gus

episodes.synopsis: To get his magic back, Constantine takes Spooner to 1939 Spain seeking the Fountain of Imperium. Mick's delicate condition has him perturbed.
episodes.title: Bad Blood

episodes.synopsis: With the Waverider in limbo, Sara and half the team find themselves stranded in a cosmic bowling alley in a game that could seal Earth's fate.
episodes.title: The Final Frame

episodes.synopsis: The Legends play a gothic role-playing game to ease their frayed nerves  but things go dreadfully awry when John's magic brings the game to life.
episodes.title: Bored on Board Onboard

episodes.synopsis: Ava tries to outwit an old foe who shows up claiming he now wants to join the Legends. Zari aims for the truth about John and the Fountain of Imperium.
episodes.title: Silence of the Sonograms

episodes.synopsis: Spooner makes a family connection in 1920s Texas after John hijacks the Waverider to jump-start his fevered quest for the Fountain of Imperium.
episodes.title: There Will Be Brood

episodes.synopsis: The power of true love meets an alien invasion when Sara and Ava take their big step just as Bishop's apocalyptic plans materialize on Earth.
episodes.title: The Fungus Amongus
